<dl id="n35215b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35215b">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35215b"> 215(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> illal / pilgrim vow</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A vow of pilgrimage might be directed to other sanctuaries than Mecca&mdash; the technical word for it (<i>ihlal</i>) is applied, for example, to the pilgrimage to Manat. <small> &ldquo;MECCA&rdquo; <a name="EBMC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBMC"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 954</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
